#: src/pages/docs/concepts/ColorPage.tsx:26
msgid "A video stream does not just carry pixel values — it carries an agreement about what those values <0>mean</0>. Three standards cover almost everything: <1>BT.601</1> (standard definition), <2>BT.709</2> (high definition — the default assumption for most content today), and <3>BT.2020</3> (ultra-HD and HDR, with a much wider color gamut). Each defines its own recipe for turning the YUV numbers in the stream back into red, green, and blue."
msgstr ""

